            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the sugar has caramelised, add your <strong>marinated basa </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until starting to brown</p><p>Once browned, add the <strong>chopped pepper</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>sliced shallot </strong>and your <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your<strong> coconut stock </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until your fish is cooked through and the sauce has thickened – this is your <strong>Vietnamese-style caramelised & braised basa</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 6,
